CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 19, 1967, pg. 3, reads: "Carl Conley Getting 'Together.'" Portion of accompanying article reads:  "Hold 'Soul' Festival in Homewood - This week, Friday, Saturday and Sunday, the City's First Annual 'Soul Festival' will be held.  The affair will be conducted on Kelly St., near Homewood Ave.  The street will be blocked off the three-day festival."
TitMainTitle: Carl Conley holding broadsides for First Annual Soul Festival, standing in interior with map of Kelly Street between Lang Avenue and Zenith Way, Homewood
